## # Resource: honeycomb.Query

Creates a query in a dataset.

> **Note** Queries can only be created or read. Any changes will result in a new query object being created, and destroying it does nothing.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as honeycomb from "@pulumi/honeycomb";

const config = new pulumi.Config();
const dataset = config.require("dataset");
const testQueryQuery = honeycomb.Query({
    calculations: [{
        op: "AVG",
        column: "duration_ms",
    }],
    filters: [{
        column: "duration_ms",
        op: ">",
        value: "200",
    }],
});
const testQueryIndex_queryQuery = new honeycomb.Query("testQueryIndex/queryQuery", {
    dataset: `%s`,
    queryJson: testQueryQuery.then(testQueryQuery => testQueryQuery.json),
});
```
